dpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2023/07/xda-terramaster-asustor-nas-hero-shot.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2023/07/xda-terramaster-asustor-nas-hero-shot.jpg\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/div\u003e \u003c/a\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan data-field=\"label\"\u003eRelated\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003ch5\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/best-nas-hard-drive/\" title=\"Best hard drives for NAS\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e Best hard drives for NAS \u003c/a\u003e \u003c/h5\u003e\u003cp\u003eIf you\u0026#39;re looking for new hard drives to increase the storage capacity of your NAS, you\u0026#39;ve come to the right place\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/div\u003e \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"usb-drives-aren-39-t-designed-for-storage-pools\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003e3 \u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan\u003e USB drives aren\u0026#39;t designed for storage pools \u003c/span\u003e \u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/11/hard-drives-caddy-case.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/11/hard-drives-caddy-case.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/11/hard-drives-caddy-case.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/11/hard-drives-caddy-case.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/11/hard-drives-caddy-case.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/11/hard-drives-caddy-case.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/11/hard-drives-caddy-case.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/11/hard-drives-caddy-case.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/11/hard-drives-caddy-case.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003cimg width=\"2100\" height=\"1181\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"hard-drives-caddy-case\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/11/hard-drives-caddy-case.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/11/hard-drives-caddy-case.jpg\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eUSB drives aren\u0026#39;t designed for storing data as part of a pool. If you\u0026#39;re running ZFS, things can become interesting when performing drive-intensive operations such as a scrub or resilver. There\u0026#39;s a higher chance the USB drive will fail before an HDD or SSD. The internal parts within USB drives don\u0026#39;t tend to be as advanced or expensive, especially compared to NAS-grade storage drives. And suing USB ports to expand your storage capacity can cause issues when working with USB hubs. It can prove difficult to determine which port is which. Finally, there\u0026#39;s no support for \u003ca href=\"https://www.howtogeek.com/134735/check-ssd-or-hdd-health-with-smart/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eS.M.A.R.T\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"not-physically-secured-to-the-nas\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003e2 \u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan\u003e Not physically secured to the NAS \u003c/span\u003e \u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/windows-11-live-usb.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/windows-11-live-usb.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/windows-11-live-usb.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/windows-11-live-usb.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/windows-11-live-usb.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/windows-11-live-usb.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/windows-11-live-usb.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/windows-11-live-usb.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/windows-11-live-usb.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003cimg width=\"3840\" height=\"2160\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"A person holding a USB drive in front of a monitor running Windows 11\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/windows-11-live-usb.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/08/windows-11-live-usb.jpg\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eNAS enclosures are precisely that. An enclosure to protect the drives running within. It\u0026#39;s also why we spend a lot on a PC case to ensure everything inside the system operates as designed and is protected against the elements. The same cannot be said for USB flash drives as they connect to external USB ports on the device. The same goes for NAS where the ports can be on the front or rear of the unit. Relying on a USB flash drive to increase the storage pool is one thing, but making sure no one accidentally removes it from the NAS is a whole different ball game.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"usb-ports-are-slower\"\u003e\u003cspan\u003e1 \u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan\u003e USB ports are slower \u003c/span\u003e \u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2023/08/synology-diskstation-ds224-plus-drives-xda.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2023/08/synology-diskstation-ds224-plus-drives-xda.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2023/08/synology-diskstation-ds224-plus-drives-xda.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2023/08/synology-diskstation-ds224-plus-drives-xda.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2023/08/synology-diskstation-ds224-plus-drives-xda.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2023/08/synology-diskstation-ds224-plus-drives-xda.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2023/08/synology-diskstation-ds224-plus-drives-xda.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2023/08/synology-diskstation-ds224-plus-drives-xda.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2023/08/synology-diskstation-ds224-plus-drives-xda.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003cimg width=\"2100\" height=\"1404\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Synology DiskStation D224+\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2023/08/synology-diskstation-ds224-plus-drives-xda.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2023/08/synology-diskstation-ds224-plus-drives-xda.jpg\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003eUSB ports have come a long way with the latest standard offering bandwidth up to 20 Gbps. For context, the latest Thunderbolt 5 can hit speeds of 80 Gbps. A NAS enclosure may only have one port that can hit 5 or 10 Gbps with perhaps an additional two that can\u0026#39;t even hit 1 Gbps. USB ports are therefore slow and you won\u0026#39;t see them fully saturated by connected USB flash drives. A SATA III slot inside the NAS will have a 6 Gbps rated speed and M.2 SSDs are even faster, depending on the CPU and available PCIe lanes.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\u003ch3 id=\"use-only-hdds-and-ssds-inside-nas\"\u003e Use only HDDs and SSDs inside NAS \u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eUSB drives have their place in your storage world. They\u0026#39;re excellent for installing operating systems (and running them, like Unraid), but they shouldn\u0026#39;t be used as part of a storage pool, no matter how many precautions you take. They\u0026#39;re not as reliable, fast, or long-lasting as other drives. You could accidentally disconnect one mid-operation, and they\u0026#39;re not great value compared to larger mechanical drives. Stick to full-size drives for storing data and use USB drives to move data, backup configuration files, and take data off-site.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv data-include-community-rating=\"false\" id=\"f301-4759-9fe04a5dd91c\" data-nosnippet=\"\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/how-to-expand-your-nas-with-usb-drives-and-why-its-not-always-a-good-idea/\"\u003e\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/04/asustor-drivestor-2-pro-gen2-as3302t-v2-hero.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/04/asustor-drivestor-2-pro-gen2-as3302t-v2-hero.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/04/asustor-drivestor-2-pro-gen2-as3302t-v2-hero.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/04/asustor-driv